procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and pregnancy testing.

procedures.name: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.label: Urine Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine samples for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy tests, and 24-hour measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Collection
procedures.description: Collection of individual fecal samples to measure copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A complete physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: Oral Dosing
procedures.description: Administration of ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water on an empty stomach.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height and weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring, detection, and follow-up of adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Infectious Disease Screening
procedures.label: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screen
procedures.description: Blood test to screen for Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening of urine for the presence of non-prescribed drugs.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Intravenous Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of a cannula into a vein to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device used for blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A catheter placed in a vein to allow for repeated blood draws. To be flushed a minimum of every 8 hours and not left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
